1. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper discusses a rule-based approach to solving constraint satisfaction problems, which is a common topic in AI research. 
2. cs.PL (Programming Languages) - The paper discusses the use of rules represented by simple first-order formulas, which is a topic related to programming languages. 
3. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) - The paper discusses various types of logical constraints, including Boolean constraints and Allen's qualitative approach to temporal logic. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the use of labeling and local consistency, which are topics related to data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses the implementation of the rule-based approach using constraint logic programming, which is a topic related to software engineering.
